sentences: Martin "Frosty" Beedle (born 18 September 1961) is a British musician who plays, produces and composes music.
In 1985 he joined the pop group Cutting Crew.
He left the band after six years in 1991 and went on to work with various acts, touring with some of them but also recording (singles/songs) with Sarah Brightman, Zucchero, Russell Watson and more.

Frosty Beedle on The Arts Show Interview with Michael Madden, 17 March 2020.
At the same time he has been holding the drum chair in the Mamma Mia show, the seventh longest running show in the London West End from year 2000.
He has also been playing with friends in a group called The Two Pianos a rock and roll band for four years.
Their last tour before COVID-19 saw them playing in Japan with the Tokyo Philharmonic Orchestra at the beginning of 2020.
Touring and west end shows being postponed he is currently working on his first solo album and has been collaborating with a number of musicians on individual projects and writing of music.
